scope_of_work.problem: The lagging on CCU8 has been damaged by birds and has left areas of exposed ducting
scope_of_work.scope:
Remove existing damaged insulation from the ductwork tops and replace with new insulation. 
Apply 0.6mm plain aluminium sheet to the insulation tops to prevent further bird attack. 
To apply silver Proclad 150 laminated self-adhesive sheet to the new ductwork and attach onto 
existing sides.
Apply a drip bead around lower areas.
scope_of_work.justification: Birds have been picking at the insulation resulting in areas of exposed ductwork open to the elements. It could be the possible cause of water ingress into the building
scope_of_work.non_approval_effect: There will be further damage to the insulation
